   <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
  <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
       <h5 class="mb-0">?? What Is This?</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
  <p><strong>Blazor DataDev</strong> is an in-memory database testing platform that allows developers to:</p>
       <ul>
   <li>Fetch schemas from multiple external databases (AWS + Internal Plato)</li>
       <li>Combine DDL files into a unified schema</li>
    <li>Load tables and data locally without a real database</li>
         <li>Test application code against local REST API</li>
   <li>Make table changes to Plato and generate migration scripts</li>
      <li>Deploy changes to production with confidence</li>
   </ul>
   <p class="mb-0"><strong>Why?</strong> Because we have <em>no dev servers</em>, this gives developers a safe local environment to test both code and database changes.</p>
  </div>
    </div>

       <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
      <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
<h5 class="mb-0">?? Primary Workflow</h5>
     </div>
   <div class="card-body">
      <ol>
      <li><strong>Fetch DDLs</strong> from 3 external DBs + Plato (Internal)</li>
     <li><strong>Merge DDLs</strong> into one file using <a href="/ddl-merger">DDL Merger</a></li>
         <li><strong>Save</strong> to Loadables/ddls/</li>
   <li><strong>Load</strong> via <a href="/startup">Startup Wizard</a></li>
    <li><strong>Add test data</strong> via CSV import or manual entry</li>
     <li><strong>Start your application</strong> pointing to <code>http://localhost:5000/api/</code></li>
   <li><strong>Test code changes</strong> and <strong>Plato table changes</strong> locally</li>
      <li><strong>Generate SQL migration scripts</strong> for Plato</li>
      <li><strong>Apply migrations</strong> to real Plato when ready</li>
  </ol>
    </div>
       </div>

    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
     <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
<h5 class="mb-0">??? Technical Stack</h5>
       </div>
   <div class="card-body">
     <ul class="mb-0">
  <li><strong>.NET 8</strong> - Runtime</li>
      <li><strong>Blazor Server</strong> - Web UI framework</li>
  <li><strong>SQLite (In-Memory)</strong> - Database engine</li>
    <li><strong>Npgsql</strong> - PostgreSQL/Redshift connectivity</li>
       <li><strong>Dapper</strong> - Data access</li>
    <li><strong>Swagger/OpenAPI</strong> - API documentation</li>
   </ul>
      </div>
